value.string: Large single story home with a large yard that needs a lot of TLC. This home is a few minutes walk to South Maui's most popular white sand beaches. Close to shopping malls, restaurants, banking, and schools. This is an older established neighborhood located in the heart of Kihei. Rock wall surrounding the property for privacy. This corner lot is just a short walk to the beach! This home won't last long. Currently configured as a 3 bed/1.5 bath main home with a 1 bed/1 bath attached ohana. Buyer and Buyer's agent to do own due diligence.

Nice Family Home in great condition in a good North Kihei neighborhood. This is a bankruptcy sale and is subject to approval of the Bankruptcy Court. Please allow 48 hours notice for showings on weekdays only please.

Kenolio Mauka is a sweet, quiet 12 home subdivision located in Kihei, one block to Sugar Beach. Home is in great shape,living room has beautiful hickory laminate floor, many windows throughout creating natural light. Sit on your front porch and watch the sunrise over Haleakala. Master bedroom is on the 1st floor, with a large bath, over sized storage under the stairwell, 2 bedroom 1 bath on the second level. Perfect for a 1st time home buyer. Recreational park located at the top of the street for owners use. Kihei canoe club, sugar beach bakery, farmers market and Uilani's shave ice just down the street. Walking distance to sugar beach and the bus stop. Very quiet peaceful setting, no road noise.

PRICED TO SELL….Don't miss this opportunity to own this well maintained 3 bedroom, 2 bath home with enclosed yard. This newly painted Piilani 1 home is situated on a corner lot with a spacious yard and only one neighbor!. The main living area has vaulted ceilings, wood laminate flooring, and an open floor plan. Well sized master suite has adjoining bath with tile, double sinks and tub/shower combo. Split AC, lanai area, storage shed and attached 2 car garage are added features of this lovely home. Centrally located...walking distance to the beach, and Piilani shopping center which offers banks, restaurants, Safeway, Starbucks, medical center, and more. Low monthly homeowner’s association fee is just $42 per month!

Welcome home to south Maui, a house with amble room in a private setting yet so very close to conveniences and the beach. This property sits back from the Keala road on a large 11,700 SQFT lot and comfortably fits three bedrooms, two bathrooms with a large back lanai. Room for children and growing things. Take time to live in this special neighborhood with the conveniences of stores, restaurants, groceries, playgrounds, volleyball, baseball, soccer, roller skating inline-hockey, beach, BBQ’s, surf, patio picnics and summertime fun. Reduce your stress levels by living a short walking distance to everything. Tenant occupied - being sold as is. Unlimited Possibilities.
Property being sold in a strictly "as-is" and "where-is" condition. Should buyer desire staking, buyer to be responsible for same. Enclosed converted garage rented separately.
